    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>GRANADA BUYS BRITISH TV ASSETS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Alan Cowell</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cowell, Alan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Granada Media PLC agrees to buy television assets of United News &amp; Media PLC for $2.64 billion, beating Carlton Communications PLC's bid for British TV dominance (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Spurred by a challenge from cable and satellite operators, Granada Media P.L.C. agreed to buy the television assets of United News and Media P.L.C. for $2.64 billion in cash and stock, beating Carlton Communications P.L.C. for dominance of Britain's most popular channel, the Independent Television Network. Granada shares, which went public this month at 515 pence, jumped to 616.5.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell (NYT)</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
